  "prompt": "What is the healthiest food I can snack on throughout the day? Must be fairly affordable + fairly tasty.",
  "response": "Choosing a healthy, affordable, and tasty snack can make a big difference in your overall diet. Here are some great options that fit the bill:\n\n---\n\n### **1. Nuts and Seeds**\n- **Examples**: Almonds, walnuts, pumpkin seeds, sunflower seeds.\n- **Why**: Packed with healthy fats, protein, and fiber. They\u2019re filling and nutritious.\n- **Tip**: Choose unsalted or lightly salted varieties to avoid excess sodium.\n\n---\n\n### **2. Fresh Fruits**\n- **Examples**: Apples, bananas, berries, oranges, grapes.\n- **Why**: Rich in vitamins, minerals, and fiber. Naturally sweet and satisfying.\n- **Tip**: Pair with a handful of nuts or a spoonful of nut butter for added protein.\n\n---\n\n### **3. Vegetables with Hummus**\n- **Examples**: Carrot sticks, cucumber slices, bell pepper strips, celery.\n- **Why**: Low in calories, high in fiber, and packed with nutrients. Hummus adds protein and flavor.\n- **Tip**: Make your own hummus for a cheaper and healthier option.\n\n---\n\n### **4. Greek Yogurt**\n- **Why**: High in protein and probiotics, which are great for gut health.\n- **Tip**: Add fresh fruit or a drizzle of honey for natural sweetness.\n\n---\n\n### **5. Hard-Boiled Eggs**\n- **Why**: An excellent source of protein and healthy fats. They\u2019re portable and filling.\n- **Tip**: Cook a batch at the start of the week for easy snacking.\n\n---\n\n### **6. Popcorn (Air-Popped)**\n- **Why**: Whole grain, low in calories, and high in fiber. A great alternative to chips.\n- **Tip**: Skip the butter and flavor with herbs, nutritional yeast, or a sprinkle of chili powder.\n\n---\n\n### **7. Oatmeal (or Overnight Oats)**\n- **Why**: High in fiber and can be customized with fruits, nuts, and seeds.\n- **Tip**: Make overnight oats for a convenient, grab-and-go snack.\n\n---\n\n### **8. Edamame**\n- **Why**: A plant-based source of protein, fiber, and vitamins. Lightly salted edamame is both tasty and nutritious.\n- **Tip**: Buy frozen edamame for an affordable and long-lasting option.\n\n---\n\n### **9. Dark Chocolate (70% or Higher)**\n- **Why**: Contains antioxidants and can satisfy sweet cravings in moderation.\n- **Tip**: Pair with a handful of nuts for a balanced snack.\n\n---\n\n### **10. Rice Cakes with Toppings**\n- **Examples**: Top with avocado, nut butter, or a slice of turkey.\n- **Why**: Light, crunchy, and customizable. Choose whole-grain rice cakes for added fiber.\n\n---\n\nThese snacks are nutrient-dense, budget-friendly, and versatile, making them perfect for grazing throughout the day!",
  "temperature": 1.0,
